{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001","id":"msg_01KbzKL63uor1XEpAFVtK4xJ","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_0158D4mhm4ekueDB2vxUHvoi","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/input/Roasted Chicken with Root Vegetables.generated.22.txt","content":"POULTRY MAINS - PAGE 47\n\nROASTED CHICKEN WITH ROOT VEGET-\nABLES\n\nIngredients:\n1 whole chicken (4-5 pounds), pat-\nted dry\n3 tablespoons olive oil\nSalt and fresh ground pepper\n2 sprigs fresh rosem-\nary\n3 sprigs fresh thyme\n6 medium potatoes, cut into 1-inch\ncubes\n4 large carrots, cut into 1-inch pie-\nces\n3 parsnips, cut into 1-inch pie-\nces\n8 pearl onions, peeled\n4 cloves garlic, sm-\nashed\n1 cup chicken broth\n\nMethod:\nPreheat oven to 425°F. Rub the chicken with 2 tablespoons olive oil, salt,\nand pepper. Stuff the cavity with rosemary and thyme.\n\nIn a large roasting pan, toss the potatoes, carrots, parsnips, onions, and\ngarlic with remaining olive oil, salt, and pepper. Arrange around the chicken\nin the pan. Pour broth around vegetables.\n\n456 ◻ Roast for 1 hour 15 minutes to 1 hour 30 minutes, until the internal\ntemperature reaches 165°F at the thickest part of the thigh. The vegetables\nshould be golden and tender.\n\nRest the chicken for 10 minutes before carving. Serve with pan jui-\nces drizzled over the vegetables.\n\nServes 4-6.\n\n*See also: Herb-Roasted Chicken (Page 52)\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":8,"cache_creation_input_tokens":617,"cache_read_input_tokens":109733,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":617},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"be930ac5-73c9-4a08-804e-ef9f978d1268","uuid":"9f09a1f8-e308-430c-8c80-d197dc1a62a7"}
